A man has been arrested over footage shot from inside a police cordon on the day Nicola Bulley was found in the River Wyre in Lancashire. The 34-year-old, from Kidderminster, Worcestershire, was arrested on suspicion of malicious communications offences and perverting the course of justice in connection with the investigation to find Ms Bulley. The arrest was confirmed this evening by Lancashire Constabulary. The footage was taken from inside a police codon on February 19, reports Metro. A spokesperson from Lancashire Constabulary said: "Our priority is, and has always been, to support Nicola’s family and the wider community in St Michael’s. "We hope this arrest provides reassurance that we take concerns seriously and will act on them." Police said he was held on Monday morning with assistance from West Mercia Police and has since been bailed with conditions.  Ms Bulley, 45, was found on the banks of the River Wyre less than a mile from where she vanished. Her family said their "worst fears had been confirmed". Their statement continued: "We will never be able to comprehend what Nikki had gone through in her last moments and that will never leave us,’ they said. "We will never forget Nikki, how could we, she was the centre of our world, she was the one who made our lives so special and nothing will cast a shadow over that. "Our girls will get the support they need from the people who love them the most."  They added: "Our hearts truly break for others who have missing loved ones. Keep that hope alive. "Finally, Nikki, you are no longer a missing person, you have been found, we can let you rest now. "We love you, always have and always will, we’ll take it from here." 